A '''nadir line''' is a line traced on the ground directly beneath an [[aircraft]] while taking [[aerial photograph]]s of the ground from above. This line connects the [[image center]]s of the successive vertical [[photograph]]s. These photographs are generally taken with some degree of ''endlap''.  Can also represent a line traced by a shipping vessel.

